tafsir[2]{c,v,t}:
  17,108,"(Saying: Glory to our Lord!) they exonerate Allah from having a son or partner. (Verily the promise of our Lord) regarding the sending of Muhammad (pbuh) (must be fulfilled) is true and must happen."
  18,3,"(Wherein they will abide for ever) they will abide in this reward forever: never to die or be removed from it;"